==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Draughtsman
<hw>Draughts"man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Draughtsmen</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
draws pleadings or other writings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who draws plans and sketches of machinery,
structures, and places; also, more generally, one who makes drawings of
any kind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A ⟦ldquo⟧man⟦rdquo⟧ or piece used in the game of
draughts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>One who drinks drams; a tippler.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Tatler.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Draughtsmanship</ent>⟦br⟧
